<dl id="n41006e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41006e">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41006e"> 6(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> the better to see / you, my dear</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">At last it becomes my turn, and the beauteous maiden with a sardonic smile leads me forth to my doom. What a room it is&mdash;what a flood of light illuminates it. <mark>&ldquo;The better to see you, my dear,&rdquo;</mark> as the Wolf observed to Red Riding Hood under somewhat similar circumstances. <small> J.B. Hall, <a name="HRRR" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#HRRR"><cite title="source">Random Records of a Reporter</cite></a> (n.d.) &lsquo;Getting a Tooth Out.&rsquo; 173</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
